### Most Critical Gap

**`red-cell-c2-dhs9`** (rate limiter) and **`red-cell-c2-f6o2`** (CTR counter race) tie for most dangerous. The CTR race is particularly severe: two concurrent encryptions for the same agent could silently reuse the same AES-CTR keystream offset — a two-time-pad — and no existing test would catch it because all tests call `encrypt_for_agent` sequentially.

### Overall Test Quality

The integration test suite (indices 52–60) is genuinely impressive: well-named tests, strong assertions, solid error-path coverage for the happy-path flows. The `database.rs` tests are especially thorough. The main systemic gaps are (1) security controls (rate limiter, RBAC positive path) that have rejection tests but no behavioral acceptance/enforcement tests, and (2) concurrent/race-condition scenarios across the crypto layer that are absent from the entire suite.
